headline: Skechers $9.4B deal, Tyson Foods beef, Twilio upgrade
summary: Skechers (SKX) has agreed to a $9.4 billion deal to be acquired and go private under 3G Capital. Tyson Foods (TSN) shares take a hit after the food producer missed revenue estimates in connection to declining demand in its meat product segments, namely beef. Twilio (TWLO) stock receives an upgrade to Hold by HSBC analysts, who also raised their price target on the company.
